1.23
log
@the OSI changed their website
@
text
@a25 14
OPTIONAL ADVERTISING CLAUSE:
Adding advertising clauses is not recommended because they accumulate
(MirOS #9 had 130 required acknowledgements, out of which several are
duplicates with only minor changes), but if this kind of crediting is
desired, the following mksh(1)-style (grouped by parentheses, separa-
ted by bars, parts can be omitted if prefixed by a question mark) ex-
pression provides a paragraph to be inserted between the two above:

 * (All a|A)dvertising materials mentioning features or use of this (
 * software|work) must display the following acknowledgement:
 *	This product includes (material|software) (provided by|devel-
 *	oped (at|?(or owned )by|under|for?( use (in|with)))) $name?(,
 *	)?( and (its|their|by other) contributors)?( (for|by) $name).

