1.10
log
@A british lawyer (although totally computer-illiterate) suggested
to rather use the word "defect" here, which strikes me as fitting.

This is still difficult. I read this as:
- bugs in upstream are not "a direct error"
- "even if advised of the...existence of a defect" means that, if
  they issue a security advisory, I still can choose to not upda-
  te (e.g. to not break more stuff)
- unknown mistakes are not "advised"
- if an unknown mistake does not prevent any "intended use of the
  work" (testing!) we're out of the wood as well
- documented mistakes shift the moving target "intended use"

Comments? This is still a draft.
@
